                            <comment id="20046" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Thu, 8 Sep 2011 11:04:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;there is two possible cases to cause this issue,&lt;br/&gt;
1, there is a bug in &quot;seq_client_proc_write_width&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
   ...&lt;br/&gt;
   cfs_down(&amp;amp;seq-&amp;gt;lcs_sem);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   rc = lprocfs_write_helper(buffer, count, &amp;amp;val);&lt;br/&gt;
   if (rc)                                &amp;lt;------- there should add a cfs_up(&amp;amp;seq-&amp;gt;lcs_sem) to release the semaphore &lt;br/&gt;
      RETURN(rc);&lt;br/&gt;
   ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2, &quot;seq_client_flush&quot; conflicts with &quot;seq_client_alloc_seq&quot;, which updates &quot;lu_client_seq-&amp;gt;lcs_space&quot; without holding&lt;br/&gt;
the &quot;lcs_sem&quot;, and &quot;seq_client_flush&quot;(called in &quot;mdc_import_event&quot; for event &quot;IMP_EVENT_INACTIVE&quot;) could reinitialize &lt;br/&gt;
it at the same time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20034" author="pjones" created="Wed, 7 Sep 2011 22:20:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HongChao&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can you please look into this one as your top priority?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
